-- Toyota U.S. sales slip 0.6 percent in Sept
-- 
-- Tue Oct 2, 2007 1:34pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/02/us-toyota-sales-idUSWNAS537820071002

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp ( 7203.T ) said on Tuesday its September U.S. sales slipped 0.6 percent from a record level of a year earlier. 

 The Japanese automaker, on track to outpace Ford Motor Co ( F.N ) as the second-largest automaker in the U.S. market, said it sold 213,043 vehicles in September, down from 222,950 vehicles a year earlier. The Toyota monthly sales results were adjusted for the number of selling days. September had 25 sales days compared with 26 days a year earlier.